Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large
#baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss
to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway
through.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Season the
@British Chicken Breasts{2} with salt and pepper.

Once hot, lay the chicken into the pan and cook until browned, ~{3-5%minutes} each
side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

While the chicken cooks, halve any thick @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%g} stems lengthways.
Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}
(or use a #garlic press{}).

Once browned, pop the chicken onto a baking tray and roast on the middle shelf of your
oven until cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes} - set your pan aside for later.

When cooked, remove from your oven, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple
of mins.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pop the @BBQ Sauce{64%g} and @Water{25%ml} into a small #bowl{} and stir
together.

Pop your (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of
@oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the broccoli and shallot. Stir-fry until the Tenderstem® starts to char
and the shallot has softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic, then turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add a splash of water and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some foil. Allow to cook
until the broccoli is tender, ~{2-3%minutes}. Transfer to your plates and drain any
excess water.

Pour the BBQ sauce into the (now empty) pan, stir well, then bring back to a bubble
and allow to reduce slightly.

Once thickened, add the cooked chicken to the pan and spoon the sauce all over to coat
it, then transfer to your plates.

Serve with the broccoli and wedges alongside, spooning any remaining sauce from the pan.
Enjoy!